<script language="JavaScript" type="text/javascript">
/***************************** Constants ********************************/

// Password strength levels
var LEVEL_0 = 0;
var LEVEL_1 = 1;
var LEVEL_2 = 2;
var LEVEL_3 = 3;
var LEVEL_4 = 4;

// Prefix for CSS class names denoting 5 different levels (0-4)
var CLASSNAME_PREFIX = 'password_strength_';
var CLASSNAME_BLANK = 'password_strength_blank';

// Array of 5 different feedback strings
var FEEDBACK_STR_ARR = new Array(
	"(invalid password)",
	"(weak password)",
	"(moderate password)",
	"(strong password)",
	"(very strong password)");

// Id of element displaying feedback about password quality
var feedbackObjId = 'idPasswordStrengthOutput';
var confirmObjId = 'idPasswordConfirmOutput';

// Regular expressions for *single char only* (literal notation for RegExp object)
var REGEXP_ALPHA = /[a-zA-Z0-9]/;
var REGEXP_NUM = /[0-9]/;
var REGEXP_LOWERCASE = /[a-z]/;


/************************** Main Functions ******************************/

/*
 * Name:		testPasswordStrength
 * Params:		formId - the id of the form containing the feedback element
 *				obj - the password input element
 * Description:	Driver function that calls level check function and displays
 *				results to the screen.
 * Returns:		void
 *
 * Important Note: Requires an element (i.e. span) with id given by 'feedbackObjId'
 * in order to post feedback to the user about password quality. Also, bind this
 * function as the 'onkeyup' event handler in order to get accurate input value.
 */
function testPasswordStrength(formId, obj) {
	
	var feedbackStr = ''; // If password blank, then clear feedback string
	var feedbackObj = document.getElementById(formId+':'+feedbackObjId);
	
	if(obj.value != '') {
		var level = getStrengthLevel(obj.value);
		feedbackObj.className = CLASSNAME_PREFIX+level;
		feedbackStr = FEEDBACK_STR_ARR[level];
	}
	else
		feedbackObj.className = CLASSNAME_BLANK;
		
	feedbackObj.innerHTML = feedbackStr;
}

function clearPasswordStrengthText(){
	var feedbackObj = document.getElementById(JSF_FORM_ID+feedbackObjId);
	feedbackObj.className = CLASSNAME_BLANK;
	feedbackObj.innerHTML = '';
}

/*
 * Name:		getStrengthLevel
 * Params:		str - the password field value
 * Description:	Function that rates a password string according to set standards.
 * Returns:		Returns the password strength level of the passed string.
 */
function getStrengthLevel(str) {

	var level = LEVEL_0;
	var isMixedCase = false;
	var numberCount = 0;
	var nonAlphaCount = 0;
	var lowerCaseCount = 0;
	var upperCaseCount = 0;

	// For Level 1: 4 character minimum
	if(str.length < 8)
		return level; // Level 0
	else
		level = LEVEL_1;

	// 8 character minimum to continue testing, else Level 1
	if(str.length < 10)
		return level; // Level 1
		
	// For each character in string
	for(var i=0; i<str.length; i++) {
		var char = str.charAt(i); // IE doesn't allow string array access str[i]
		// Number
		if(isNumber(char))
			numberCount++;
		// Non-alpha
		else if(isNonAlpha(char))
			nonAlphaCount++;
		// Alpha
		else {
			if(isAlphaLowerCase(char))
				lowerCaseCount++;
			else
				upperCaseCount++;
		}
	}
	
	// First determine if mixed case
	isMixedCase = lowerCaseCount > 0 && upperCaseCount > 0;
	
	// For Level 2: 1+ alphabetic AND either mixed case or 1+ number or 1+ non-alphanumeric character
	if((lowerCaseCount > 0 || upperCaseCount > 0) &&
			(isMixedCase || numberCount > 0 || nonAlphaCount > 0))
		level = LEVEL_2;

	// For Level 3: 8 character minimum (already guaranteed) and mixed case 
	if(!isMixedCase)
		return level;
	
	// Also for Level 3: 1+ number and 1+ non-alphanumeric character
	if(numberCount > 0 && nonAlphaCount > 0)
		level = LEVEL_3;
		
	// For Level 4: 15 character minimum
	if(str.length < 15)
		return level;
	
	// Also for Level 4: 2+ lower case, and 2+ upper case, and 2+ numbers, and 2+ non-alphanumeric characters		
	if(lowerCaseCount > 1 && upperCaseCount > 1 && numberCount > 1 && nonAlphaCount > 1)
		level = LEVEL_4;

	return level;
}

/*
 * Name:		testConfirmPasswordMatch
 * Params:		formId - the id of the form containing the feedback element
 *				passwordId - the id of the password input element
 *				confirmObj - the confirm password input element
 * Description:	Function that checks password and confirm password fields for
 *				equality.
 * Returns:		Returns true if passwords match, else false.
 */
function testConfirmPasswordMatch(formId, passwordId, confirmObj) {

	var passwordObj = document.getElementById(formId+':'+passwordId);
	var errorMsg = '';
	
	if(confirmObj.value != '' && confirmObj.value != passwordObj.value)
		errorMsg = "MISSING: password_confirm_error_do_not_match :MISSING";
	
	document.getElementById(formId+':'+confirmObjId).innerHTML = errorMsg;
}


/************************* Helper Functions *****************************/

/*
 * Name:		isNumber
 * Params:		char - the character to be checked
 * Description:	Function that determines whether passed char is a number.
 * Returns:		Returns true if number or false if not.
 */
function isNumber(char) {
	return char.match(REGEXP_NUM) != null;
}

/*
 * Name:		isNonAlpha
 * Params:		char - the character to be checked
 * Description:	Function that determines whether passed char is a number.
 * Returns:		Returns true if number or false if not.
 */
function isNonAlpha(char) {
	return char.match(REGEXP_ALPHA) == null; // Match everything but alpha
}

/*
 * Name:		isAlphaLowerCase
 * Params:		char - the character to be checked
 * Description:	Function that determines whether passed letter is lower-case.
 * Returns:		Returns true if lower-case or false if upper-case. Also,
 *				returns false if passed char is non-alphabet
 */
function isAlphaLowerCase(char) {
	if(isNonAlpha(char) || isNumber(char))
		return false;
	else
		return char.match(REGEXP_LOWERCASE) != null;
}
</script>
<script type="text/javascript">
var JSF_FORM_ID = "changePasswordForm:";
var validateFlag = true;
var doSubmit = true;

function init() {
	GenericOnLoad.GenericHandler();
	
	// check if there was a password change and we need to logoff
	if(false){
		if(top && top.logoffEIP){
			alert("Password successfully changed. You will now be logged off.");
			top.logoffEIP();
			return;
		}
	}

	//
	// make sure the selected menu is the my account menu
	//
	setSelectedMenu("myAccountMenuItem","myAccountPage");
	
	resetValues("oldPassword");
	resetValues("idPassword");
	resetValues("idConfirmedPassword");
	
	// set focus on the password field
	setFocus(document.getElementById(JSF_FORM_ID + "oldPassword"));
	updateLanguage();
}

function resetValues(fieldName){
	var fieldObj = document.getElementById(JSF_FORM_ID + fieldName);
	if(objExists(fieldObj)){
		fieldObj.value = "";
	}
}

function beforeSubmit() {	
	if (doSubmit == false) {
		return false;
	}
	if (validateFlag == true) {
		if (validateForm()) {
			enableAllFields();
			startProcessingImage();
			doSubmit = false;		//no double submit
			return true;
		} else {
			return false;
		}
	} else {
		enableAllFields();
		startProcessingImage();
		doSubmit = false;		//no double submit
		return true;
	}
}

function enableAllFields(){
	var disabled = false;
}

function validateForm() {

 	ErrorManager.init();
	
	//password - check for local user
	var password = JSF_FORM_ID + "idPassword"; 
	var confirmPassword = JSF_FORM_ID + "idConfirmedPassword"; 
	var oldPassword = JSF_FORM_ID + "oldPassword"; 

	var passwordObj = document.getElementById(password);
	var confirmPasswordObj = document.getElementById(confirmPassword);
	var oldPasswordObj = document.getElementById(oldPassword);

	//
	// if one of the password fields is not empty -> validate password change
	//
	if(passwordObj!=null && confirmPasswordObj!=null && oldPasswordObj!=null &&
 		( !checkIfFieldIsEmpty(oldPasswordObj) || !checkIfFieldIsEmpty(passwordObj) || !checkIfFieldIsEmpty(confirmPasswordObj)) ){
	
		ErrorManager.validateFieldNotEmpty(oldPassword, "Please enter the current password.");
		
		ErrorManager.validateFieldNotEmpty(password, "Please enter a new password.");
		if (ErrorManager.formValidated) {
			if (passwordObj.length > 255 || passwordObj.length < 8) {
				ErrorManager.handleError(passwordObj, "Password length must be between 8 and 255 characters.", true);
			}
		}

		ErrorManager.validateFieldNotEmpty(confirmPassword, "Please confirm the password.");
		if (ErrorManager.formValidated) {
			ErrorManager.validateComparedPasswords(password, confirmPassword, "The New password and Confirm password fields do not match.");
			if(!ErrorManager.formValidated){
				clearPasswordStrengthText();
			}	
		}
	}

	return ErrorManager.finalize();
}

//in case user changed language - when page loads we check and modify the value if needed.
function updateLanguage(){
	var selected = document.getElementById(JSF_FORM_ID+"idLanguageSelect");
	if(window.top.APPLICATION_LANGUAGE != selected.value){
		window.top.APPLICATION_LANGUAGE = selected.value;
	}
}
</script>
